article.headline: Creighton 60, Evansville 56
article.story: EVANSVILLE, Ind. (AP) -- Johnny Mathies scored 17 points to lead Creighton to a 60-56 win over Evansville on Tuesday night. Anthony Tolliver had 13 points and 12 rebounds and Josh Dotzler added 11 points for the Bluejays (17-5, 11-3 Missouri Valley Conference). Jason Holsinger led Evansville (6-16, 2-12) with 14 points and Bradley Strickland added 13. It was Evansville's ninth loss in 10 games, while Creighton remained in the conference lead. Evansville led 33-28 at halftime, but Creighton chipped away in the second half and finally took a 53-52 lead on a Dotzler jumper with two minutes remaining. Jimmy Motz followed with a 3-pointer for Creighton with 56 seconds left, and the Purple Aces never got closer than three points the rest of the way. Creighton held Evansville to 29 percent shooting in the second half. The Bluejays made 8-of-20 3-pointers, including four by Mathies.
